### useRef vs useState

useRef returns a mutable object that persists across renders without causing re-renders when mutated. Use it for DOM access, timers, or values that don't need to trigger updates. useState triggers re-renders on changes.

```typescript
const inputRef = useRef(null);
const intervalRef = useRef(null);

const focusInput = () => inputRef.current.focus();
const startTimer = () => {
  intervalRef.current = setInterval(() => {}, 1000);
};
```

**Common interview trap:** Mutating ref.current doesn't trigger re-render, so don't use refs for values that need to update the UI.

